---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About Us | Capstone Project Platform">
  <main>
    <section class="wrap page-head">
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1 class="page-title">About the platform</h1>
      <p class="page-sub">
        The platform is planned as a lightweight archive for capstone project work, learning outcomes, and public-facing project stories.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="wrap simple-section">
      <div class="simple-grid">
        <h2>First-version aim</h2>
        <div class="simple-copy">
          <p>
            The first version establishes the platform structure before expanding the content. It makes clear where project stories, background information, and maintenance guidance belong.
          </p>
          <p>
            This version avoids login, CMS editing, approval workflow, database backend, and individual project app hosting. The site remains static and maintainable through structured content files.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
